        <p> After a really good food and nice chat with the table neighbors over God, the mountains and the weather, we decided: there is still something going on! And lo and behold - the sun was actually brief. So go: along the stream, nimble step, fresh air. From Baad to H&ouml;fle, accompanied by the rippling of the Breitach, always towards the dessert. Because drinks and dessert were waiting in hell - included with panorama. Vacation as he should be. </p>
        <p> But wait - more is possible! We didn't want to go back by bus yet. So on - half along the slope, through forest and meadow, to Riezlern. On the way we found a few tiny wild strawberries. I don't know how they survived, but they were there - and delicious! Briefly rinsed in the stream and nibbled directly. Gourmet enjoyment &agrave; la Alpen-Edition. </p>
        <p> In Riezlern we got a bus ticket back to the campsite. The next rain area piled up on the horizon - presumably that from yesterday, only with reinforcements. But as gracious as it was, we let us eat in peace - with a mountain view and residual sun. </p>
        <p> Then: rain. Again. So back into the car, make you comfortable. Watch a bit of films, write blog, wash the laundry-the classic camping mix of everyday life and adventure. </p>
        <p> In the end it was a typical day of vacation: first rain, then sun, then cake - and everything is fine. </p>
